---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import PolicyBlock from '../components/PolicyBlock.astro';
import CalloutBand from '../components/CalloutBand.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Ollie's Law — Paws on Longmeadow">
  <Hero
    title="Safety Isn't Optional. It's the Standard."
    subtitle="Massachusetts pet care regulations exist for a reason, and we take them seriously."
  />

  <PolicyBlock heading="Why this law exists">
    <p>
      Ollie's Law is named after a dog. In 2020, a seven-month-old labradoodle named Ollie was
      severely injured by other dogs at a Massachusetts boarding facility. He spent two months in
      veterinary care before he died of his injuries, and his owner was never given a clear answer
      about how it happened. Her fight for accountability became Ollie's Law, which Governor Healey
      signed in 2024.
    </p>
    <p>
      We take that seriously. Not because we are required to, but because it is the kind of
      accountability this industry should have. We have a dog named Ollie too. We know what it means
      to love one.
    </p>
  </PolicyBlock>

  <PolicyBlock heading="What it means for us">
    <p>
      Paws on Longmeadow is fully compliant with Ollie's Law. We operate under a Special Permit from
      the Town of Sharon Zoning Board of Appeals, hold a valid kennel license, and keep complete
      health and compliance records for every dog in our care. Our property is inspected annually by
      the Town of Sharon Animal Control Officer.
    </p>
  </PolicyBlock>

  <PolicyBlock heading="What it means for you">
    <p>
      <strong>Rabies certificate.</strong> We keep a current Rabies vaccination certificate on file
      for every dog. A note with only the date and expiration is no longer enough; we need the full
      certificate.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Dog license.</strong> Massachusetts requires all dogs over six months to be licensed
      with their city or town, and we keep a record of that valid license.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Collar and tags.</strong> Dogs wear a collar or harness with a current Rabies tag and
      an inscribed municipal dog tag.
    </p>
    <p>
      For more detail, visit the state's official
      <a href="https://www.mass.gov/info-details/ollies-law-information">Ollie's Law page at mass.gov</a>.
    </p>
  </PolicyBlock>

  <CalloutBand heading="Questions?" text="Reach out any time." ctaLabel="Contact us" ctaHref="/contact" />
</BaseLayout>
